### Step 4 вЂ” Country Profile Window

#### [NEW] [CountryProfile.tsx](file:///c:/Users/zephy/Documents/Brinkmanship/ui/src/app/components/CountryProfile.tsx)

Popout `<SovereignWindow>` showing:
- **Leader name** + **sovereign title** (from `gameState.player_profile`)
- **Country name** + current **flavor label** / **perceived flavor label**
- Key stats: AUT, STB, APP, GFI as large glowing numerals
- Estate influence as a horizontal bar breakdown (Royal Diwan / Armed Forces / Oil Workers)
- Current ideological position badge (flavor label text, color-coded by quadrant)

Opened via a "Profile" button in the header toolbar.

---

### Step 5 вЂ” Satellite World Map

#### [MODIFY] [TacticalMap.tsx](file:///c:/Users/zephy/Documents/Brinkmanship/ui/src/app/components/TacticalMap.tsx)

Replace current static map with a `react-simple-maps` `ComposableMap` (already installed) enhanced with:
- **Satellite aesthetic**: dark fill `#0d1117` with country borders in `rgba(255,176,0,0.3)` (amber amber grid) вЂ” this gives the "satellite surveillance" look without a paid tile provider
- **Zoom/pan**: wrap in `react-zoom-pan-pinch`'s `<TransformWrapper>` + `<TransformComponent>` (install needed)
- **Country hover**: amber glow `stroke` on hover; tooltip shows country name
- **Expand button**: opens map as maximized `<SovereignWindow>`

> **Note on satellite tiles:** Using Mapbox/Leaflet requires an API key and a Next.js server component workaround. For Phase 18, we use `react-simple-maps` + dark SVG styling to achieve the "surveillance aesthetic." Real satellite imagery can be added in Phase 19 if user provides a Mapbox token.

---

### Step 6 вЂ” page.tsx Restructure

#### [MODIFY] [page.tsx](file:///c:/Users/zephy/Documents/Brinkmanship/ui/src/app/page.tsx)

Wrap everything in `<WindowProvider>`. Replace the fixed CSS grid with a `relative min-h-screen` canvas. Each panel becomes a `<SovereignWindow>`. Header toolbar gets window-toggle buttons:

```
[ANCHOR] [RECALL] [SWAP CONFIG в–ѕ] [PROFILE] [MAP в¤ў] [START CHRONOS в–¶]
```

The `[PROFILE]` button opens the `country` window. The `[MAP в¤ў]` button maximizes the worldMap window.

